# Implementation Plan - Interactive Editor & Layout Fixes

The user needs to edit slides AND requires immediate fixes for broken layouts (overflows, collisions).

## Goals
1.  **Fix Layouts**: Address "awful" spacing in Grid (text overflow) and Split (collisions).
2.  **Interaction**: Enable inline text editing and image drag-and-drop.

## 1. Core Interactive Components
These components will replace static HTML tags in all templates.

### `EditableText.tsx`
-   **Props**: `value`, `onChange`, `className`, `tagName` (h1/p/div), `multiline` (bool).
-   **Implementation**: Use `contentEditable` with `suppressContentEditableWarning`.
-   **Style**: transparent background, inherits font styles, shows dashed border on hover/focus.

### `EditableImage.tsx`
-   **Props**: `src`, `alt`, `className`, `onUpload`, `isBackground`.
-   **Implementation**:
    -   Displays image.
    -   **Drag & Drop**: Native HTML5 DnD listeners.
    -   **Click**: Triggers hidden `<input type="file">`.
    -   **Style**: Shows "Change Image" overlay on hover.

## 2. Template Refactoring & Repairs

### [GridSlide.tsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slideshow/src/components/Templates/GridSlide.tsx) (Repair + Interact)
-   **Problem**: Fixed height columns cause text overlap.
-   **Fix**:
    -   Use CSS Grid (`grid-cols-2`) instead of Flex or fixed width.
    -   Allow cards to grow vertically.
    -   Add `overflow-y-auto` or simpler clamping.
-   **Interact**: Wrap items in `EditableText`.

### [SplitSlide.tsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slideshow/src/components/Templates/SplitSlide.tsx) (Repair + Interact)
-   **Problem**: Text hits image; image placeholder is ugly.
-   **Fix**:
    -   Increase gap (`gap-12`).
    -   Enforce max-height on image container.
    -   Better flex grow/shrink logic.
-   **Interact**: `EditableText` for title/body, `EditableImage` for the split image.

### [HeroSlide.tsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slideshow/src/components/Templates/HeroSlide.tsx) (Interact)
-   **Interact**: Make Title/Subtitle editable. Add `EditableImage` for the background (a bit trickier layout-wise, but doable).

